Overview of packaging challenges
Consumer packaging industry faces evolving challenges including material shortages and shifting consumer preferences toward sustainability

Post-pandemic market shows increased online buying, requiring more robust packaging solutions for shipping 

Quality requirements have significantly increased, especially regarding particle contamination in specialized packaging applications

Regulatory environments are becoming more stringent, requiring higher standards for container closure integrity and performance

Environmental considerations are driving changes in material selection as many businesses aim to eliminate plastics in favor of paper-based containers
